<div class="container">
    <h1>{{title}}</h1>
    <p class="welcome-message">{{message}}</p>
    
    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>This is a MVC (Model-View-Controller) boilerplate for NestJS applications.</p>
        
        <h3>Directory Structure:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>src/controllers/</strong> - Contains controller files that handle HTTP requests</li>
            <li><strong>src/models/</strong> - Contains entity/model files for database tables</li>
            <li><strong>src/views/</strong> - Contains Handlebars templates for rendering HTML</li>
            <li><strong>src/services/</strong> - Contains service files for business logic</li>
            <li><strong>public/</strong> - Contains static assets (CSS, JS, images)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
